Part 1: Create hierarchy as in following figure
Shape
  Circle
  Rectangle
    Square

Part 2: Add attributes to your shapes(radius, width, length)

Part 3: Add constructors to your shapes to initialize instance fields

Part 4: Override toString method in each shape

Part 5: Create class GeometryApp, and create instances of you shapes and print them(but debug them before)

Part 6: create method getArea, getPerimeter and calculate them